## Test Protocol

### Phase 0: Camera Capability Test

**Goal:** Determine what your cameras actually support
```bash
# Test if cameras can capture at 90fps
ffmpeg -f v4l2 -framerate 90 -video_size 1920x1080 -i /dev/video0 \
  -f null - 2>&1 | grep -E "(fps|frame)"

# If 90fps doesn't work, try lower framerates
for fps in 90 60 30; do
  echo "Testing ${fps} fps..."
  ffmpeg -f v4l2 -framerate ${fps} -video_size 1920x1080 -i /dev/video0 \
    -t 5 -f null - 2>&1 | grep "frame"
done

# Test both cameras simultaneously (stereo)
ffmpeg -f v4l2 -framerate 90 -video_size 1920x1080 -i /dev/video0 \
  -f v4l2 -framerate 90 -video_size 1920x1080 -i /dev/video2 \
  -filter_complex "[0:v][1:v]hstack" \
  -t 5 -f null - 2>&1
```

**Record:**
- [ ] Maximum framerate at each resolution
- [ ] Pixel format (yuyv422, mjpeg, etc.)
- [ ] USB bandwidth limitations
- [ ] Any dropped frames or errors

**Results:**
```
Camera Model: _______________________
Maximum FPS at 1920×1080: _____ fps
Maximum FPS at 1280×720: _____ fps
Pixel Format: _______________________
```

---

### Phase 1: Encoding Speed Tests

**Goal:** Find which resolution can encode <11ms per frame

Create test script `test_encoding_speed.sh`:
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# test_encoding_speed.sh - Test encoding speed for different resolutions and presets

# Create results directory
mkdir -p results
echo "Resolution,Preset,EncodingFPS,TimePerFrame_ms,PixelCount,Pass" > results/encoding_results.csv

# Test configurations
RESOLUTIONS=(
  "3840x1080"  # Config A
  "3200x900"   # Config B
  "2560x720"   # Config C
  "3840x1200"  # Config D
  "3200x1600"  # Config E
  "2560x1280"  # Config F
)

PRESETS=("p1" "p2" "p3")  # Fastest to medium-fast

# Generate test pattern if needed
generate_test_pattern() {
  local res=$1
  local output="test_pattern_${res}.yuv"
  
  if [ ! -f "$output" ]; then
    echo "Generating test pattern for ${res}..."
    ffmpeg -f lavfi -i "testsrc=size=${res}:rate=90" \
      -t 10 -pix_fmt yuv420p "$output" -y
  fi
}

# Main test loop
for res in "${RESOLUTIONS[@]}"; do
  width=$(echo $res | cut -d'x' -f1)
  height=$(echo $res | cut -d'x' -f2)
  pixels=$((width * height))
  
  echo ""
  echo "============================================"
  echo "Testing resolution: ${res} (${pixels} pixels)"
  echo "============================================"
  
  # Generate test pattern
  generate_test_pattern "$res"
  
  for preset in "${PRESETS[@]}"; do
    echo ""
    echo "Testing preset: ${preset}"
    
    # Run encoding test
    ffmpeg -f rawvideo -pix_fmt yuv420p -s ${res} -r 90 \
      -i test_pattern_${res}.yuv \
      -c:v h264_nvenc \
      -preset ${preset} \
      -tune ll \
      -b:v 15M -maxrate 15M -minrate 15M \
      -g 12 -bf 0 \
      -t 10 \
      -f null - 2>&1 | tee results/log_${res}_${preset}.txt
    
    # Extract encoding speed
    speed=$(grep "speed=" results/log_${res}_${preset}.txt | tail -1 | \
            sed -n 's/.*speed=\s*\([0-9.]*\)x.*/\1/p')
    
    if [ -z "$speed" ] || [ "$speed" = "0" ]; then
      echo "ERROR: Could not extract encoding speed"
      echo "${res},${preset},ERROR,ERROR,${pixels},FAIL" >> results/encoding_results.csv
      continue
    fi
    
    # Calculate encoding FPS and time per frame
    encoding_fps=$(echo "scale=2; $speed * 90" | bc)
    time_per_frame=$(echo "scale=2; 1000 / $encoding_fps" | bc)
    
    # Check if it passes (<11ms per frame)
    pass="FAIL"
    if (( $(echo "$time_per_frame < 11" | bc -l) )); then
      pass="PASS"
    fi
    
    echo "Encoding FPS: ${encoding_fps}"
    echo "Time per frame: ${time_per_frame} ms"
    echo "Result: ${pass}"
    
    # Save results
    echo "${res},${preset},${encoding_fps},${time_per_frame},${pixels},${pass}" >> results/encoding_results.csv
  done
done

echo ""
echo "============================================"
echo "Testing complete! Results saved to results/encoding_results.csv"
echo "============================================"
echo ""
echo "Passing configurations (encoding time <11ms):"
grep "PASS" results/encoding_results.csv | column -t -s,
```

**Run the test:**
```bash
chmod +x test_encoding_speed.sh
./test_encoding_speed.sh
```

**Expected output format:**
```csv
Resolution,Preset,EncodingFPS,TimePerFrame_ms,PixelCount,Pass
3840x1080,p1,820.50,1.22,4147200,PASS
3840x1080,p2,650.25,1.54,4147200,PASS
3200x900,p1,1125.00,0.89,2880000,PASS
...
```

**Pass Criteria:** Time per frame < 11ms (encoding FPS > 8.18x playback speed = 737fps)

