### Phase 2: Bitrate vs Quality Sweep

**Goal:** Find minimum bitrate for acceptable VR quality

Create test script `test_bitrate_quality.sh`:
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# test_bitrate_quality.sh - Test quality at different bitrates

# Configuration (set based on Phase 1 results)
RESOLUTION="3840x1080"  # Your best resolution from Phase 1
PRESET="p1"             # Your best preset from Phase 1

# Create results directory
mkdir -p results
echo "Bitrate_Mbps,PSNR_dB,VMAF,FileSize_MB,QualityRating" > results/quality_results.csv

# Bitrate range to test
BITRATES=(6 8 10 12 15 20 25 30)

# Generate test pattern (10 seconds)
if [ ! -f "test_stereo.yuv" ]; then
  echo "Generating test pattern..."
  ffmpeg -f lavfi -i "testsrc=size=${RESOLUTION}:rate=90" \
    -t 10 -pix_fmt yuv420p test_stereo.yuv -y
fi

echo ""
echo "============================================"
echo "Testing bitrate vs quality for ${RESOLUTION}"
echo "============================================"

for bitrate in "${BITRATES[@]}"; do
  echo ""
  echo "Testing bitrate: ${bitrate}M"
  
  # Encode
  ffmpeg -f rawvideo -pix_fmt yuv420p -s ${RESOLUTION} -r 90 \
    -i test_stereo.yuv \
    -c:v h264_nvenc -preset ${PRESET} -tune ll \
    -b:v ${bitrate}M -maxrate ${bitrate}M -minrate ${bitrate}M \
    -g 12 -bf 0 \
    results/encoded_${bitrate}M.mp4 -y
  
  # Measure PSNR
  ffmpeg -f rawvideo -pix_fmt yuv420p -s ${RESOLUTION} -r 90 -i test_stereo.yuv \
    -i results/encoded_${bitrate}M.mp4 \
    -lavfi "[0:v][1:v]psnr=stats_file=results/psnr_${bitrate}M.log" \
    -f null - 2>&1
  
  # Measure VMAF (may take time)
  echo "Computing VMAF (this may take a few minutes)..."
  ffmpeg -f rawvideo -pix_fmt yuv420p -s ${RESOLUTION} -r 90 -i test_stereo.yuv \
    -i results/encoded_${bitrate}M.mp4 \
    -lavfi "[0:v][1:v]libvmaf=log_path=results/vmaf_${bitrate}M.json:n_threads=8" \
    -f null - 2>&1
  
  # Extract metrics
  psnr=$(grep "average" results/psnr_${bitrate}M.log | awk '{print $5}' | cut -d':' -f2)
  vmaf=$(jq '.pooled_metrics.vmaf.mean' results/vmaf_${bitrate}M.json 2>/dev/null || echo "N/A")
  size=$(du -m results/encoded_${bitrate}M.mp4 | cut -f1)
  
  # Quality rating
  quality="Unknown"
  if [ "$vmaf" != "N/A" ]; then
    if (( $(echo "$vmaf >= 90" | bc -l) )); then
      quality="Excellent"
    elif (( $(echo "$vmaf >= 80" | bc -l) )); then
      quality="Good"
    elif (( $(echo "$vmaf >= 70" | bc -l) )); then
      quality="Acceptable"
    else
      quality="Poor"
    fi
  fi
  
  echo "PSNR: ${psnr} dB"
  echo "VMAF: ${vmaf}"
  echo "File Size: ${size} MB"
  echo "Quality: ${quality}"
  
  # Save results
  echo "${bitrate},${psnr},${vmaf},${size},${quality}" >> results/quality_results.csv
done

echo ""
echo "============================================"
echo "Quality testing complete! Results saved to results/quality_results.csv"
echo "============================================"
echo ""
cat results/quality_results.csv | column -t -s,
```

**Run the test:**
```bash
chmod +x test_bitrate_quality.sh
./test_bitrate_quality.sh
```

**Quality Targets for VR Telepresence:**
- **Minimum acceptable:** PSNR >32 dB, VMAF >70
- **Good quality:** PSNR >36 dB, VMAF >80
- **Excellent quality:** PSNR >40 dB, VMAF >90

**Bitrate estimation per second:**
```
Bitrate (Mbps) × 1 second = MB/second
15 Mbps = 1.875 MB/s = 112.5 MB/minute = 6.75 GB/hour

Typical WiFi 6 bandwidth: 100-600 Mbps (plenty of headroom)
Typical 5G bandwidth: 50-300 Mbps
```

