### Phase 3: Codec Comparison (H.264 vs H.265)

**Goal:** Compare H.264 and H.265 performance

**Only test H.265 if:**
- H.264 encoding is fast enough (<11ms)
- Network bandwidth is constrained
- You want better quality at same bitrate
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# test_codec_comparison.sh - Compare H.264 vs H.265

RESOLUTION="3840x1080"  # Your best resolution
PRESET="p1"
BITRATE="15"

echo "Testing H.264 NVENC..."
ffmpeg -f rawvideo -pix_fmt yuv420p -s ${RESOLUTION} -r 90 -i test_stereo.yuv \
  -c:v h264_nvenc -preset ${PRESET} -tune ll \
  -b:v ${BITRATE}M -maxrate ${BITRATE}M -minrate ${BITRATE}M \
  -g 12 -bf 0 \
  -t 10 -f null - 2>&1 | tee h264_test.log

h264_speed=$(grep "speed=" h264_test.log | tail -1 | sed -n 's/.*speed=\s*\([0-9.]*\)x.*/\1/p')
h264_time=$(echo "scale=2; 1000 / ($h264_speed * 90)" | bc)

echo ""
echo "Testing H.265 NVENC..."
ffmpeg -f rawvideo -pix_fmt yuv420p -s ${RESOLUTION} -r 90 -i test_stereo.yuv \
  -c:v hevc_nvenc -preset ${PRESET} -tune ll \
  -b:v ${BITRATE}M -maxrate ${BITRATE}M -minrate ${BITRATE}M \
  -g 12 -bf 0 \
  -t 10 -f null - 2>&1 | tee h265_test.log

h265_speed=$(grep "speed=" h265_test.log | tail -1 | sed -n 's/.*speed=\s*\([0-9.]*\)x.*/\1/p')
h265_time=$(echo "scale=2; 1000 / ($h265_speed * 90)" | bc)

echo ""
echo "============================================"
echo "Codec Comparison Results"
echo "============================================"
echo "H.264 NVENC: ${h264_time} ms/frame"
echo "H.265 NVENC: ${h265_time} ms/frame"
echo ""

if (( $(echo "$h264_time < 11" | bc -l) )); then
  echo "✅ H.264 passes latency requirement"
else
  echo "❌ H.264 fails latency requirement"
fi

if (( $(echo "$h265_time < 11" | bc -l) )); then
  echo "✅ H.265 passes latency requirement"
else
  echo "❌ H.265 fails latency requirement"
fi
```

**Decision criteria:**
- If H.265 encoding is still <11ms → use H.265 (better quality)
- If H.265 encoding is >11ms → use H.264 (faster)

**Paper finding:** H.265 requires ~7.5% **less** bitrate than H.264 for same quality, but only ~1ms slower encoding

